about.description:
WIM research and algorithms using code files and science notebooks with examples,
explanations and specifications.

name: pywim
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pywim" %}
{% set version = "0.1.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "f62c6b3416e69248c5086dac57cc8e6cd8435ef1ee0b85a5d9e34cdd58feaf66" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 1000
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt
  skip: True  # [py2k and py<35]

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - numpy >=1.12
    - scipy
    - matplotlib
    - pandas
    - ipython
    - sqlalchemy
    - statsmodels
    - llvmlite
    - scikit-learn
    - jupyter
    - numba
    - h5py
    - peakutils

test:
  imports:
    - pywim

about:
  home: https://github.com/OpenWIM/pywim
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'https://github.com/OpenWIM/pywim'

  description: |
    WIM research and algorithms using code files and science notebooks with examples, 
    explanations and specifications.
  doc_url: https://pywim.readthedocs.io
  dev_url: https://github.com/OpenWIM/pywim

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xmnlab
